@facturion/codelists
=====================

This package is licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE).

It incorporates or derives data from the following upstream sources. The code
values and English names of standardized code lists are facts drawn from public
standards; the curated subsets, the multilingual labels sourced as noted below,
and all explanatory "hint" text are the original contribution of this package.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Unicode CLDR (Common Locale Data Repository)
  Used for: localized country and currency display names (all locales).
  Source:   https://github.com/unicode-org/cldr-json
  License:  Unicode License v3 (SPDX: Unicode-3.0) — permissive, MIT-compatible.
            https://www.unicode.org/license.txt

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OpenPEPPOL eDEC Code Lists
  Used for: Peppol participant identifier (EAS) scheme codes, names and the
            per-scheme country association.
  Source:   https://github.com/OpenPEPPOL/edec-codelists
  License:  Apache License 2.0.
            https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
UN/CEFACT code lists
  Used for: units of measure (Rec 20/21), payment means (UNTDID 4461), VAT
            category codes (UNTDID 5305), invoice type codes (UNCL 1001),
            tax-point date codes (UNTDID 2005), item classification schemes
            (UNTDID 7143).
  Codes and standard names are published international-standard data.
  Reference: https://unece.org/trade/uncefact/

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ISO 3166-1 (country codes) and ISO 4217 (currency codes)
  Code values are published ISO standard identifiers.
